					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Circle to circle collision detection is easy, or at least it was when I implemented it in Thwaite (missiles to explosions) and ZapPing (ball to paddle ends). First do the rectangle test, then look up (x2-x1)^2 and (y2-y1)^2 in a lookup table. You have a collision if (x2-x1)^2 + (y2-y1)^2 &gt; (r1+r2)^2.<br /><br />Circle to square, or in fact the more general case of two axis-aligned rounded rectangles, is quick too. Do you want me to draw a diagram explaining it?</div>

